-- ECB funding to Italian banks rise to 216.4 bln euros in May
-- By Valentina Za
-- Mon Jun 09, 2014 05:16AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, June 9 (Reuters) - European Central Bank funds to Italian banks stood at 216.4 billion euros ($294.63 billion) in May, up 5.9 billion euros from a month earlier, Bank of Italy data showed on Monday.

Italian banks held 32.1 billion euros in funds borrowed at the main ECB tenders at the end of May, up from 23.5 billion euros a month earlier.